      • add

        public void add(java.lang.Comparable object,
       java.lang.Comparable attribute)
         throws java.lang.ClassCastException
        Description copied from interface: Relation
        Adds the pair (object, attribute) to this relation.

        If object is not yet contained in the object set of this relation it will be added to that set. Similarly, if attribute is not yet contained in the attribute set of this relation it will be added to that set.

        If object is null no pair will be added to this relation but attribute will be added to the attribute set of this relation. Similarly, if attribute is null no pair will be added to this relation but object will be added to the object set of this relation.

        Specified by:
        add in interface Relation
        Parameters:
        object - the object. If this is null, only the attribute will be added to the attribute set.
        attribute - the attribute. If this is null, only the object will be added to the object set
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassCastException - if object is not mutually comparable with the objects contained in the object set of this relation or attribute is not mutually comparable with the attributes contained in the attribute set of this relation.

      • commonAttributes

        public ComparableSet commonAttributes(java.util.Collection<java.lang.Comparable> coll)
                               throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Description copied from interface: Relation
        Returns a set of attributes which are associated with all the specified objects.

        More formally, this method returns a set that contains all attributes a for which it is true that for all objects o that are contained in coll the pair (o, a) is contained in this relation.

        Specified by:
        commonAttributes in interface Relation
        Parameters:
        coll - a collection of objects.
        Returns:
        the set of attributes all objects contained in the collection objects have.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if objects is null or one of the elements contained in objects is not contained in the object set of this relation.

      • contains

        public boolean contains(java.lang.Object object,
               java.lang.Object attribute)
        Description copied from interface: Relation
        Returns true if and only if the pair (object, attribute) is contained in this relation.

        If object is null this method will return true if and only if attribute is contained in the attribute set of this relation. Similarly, if attribute is null this method will return true if and only if object is contained in the object set of this relation.

        Specified by:
        contains in interface Relation
        Parameters:
        object - the object.
        attribute - the attribute.
        Returns:
        true, iff the pair (object, attribute) is contained in the relation.

        public boolean disallowChanges()
        Description copied from interface: Relation
        Activates write protection on this relation.

        After this method has been called, this relation shall be unmodifiable, i.e. if there is a call attempting to change the contents of this set, an exception will be thrown. Note that the implementation of this method is optional in classes that implement this interface.

        Specified by:
        disallowChanges in interface Relation
        Returns:

      • remove

        public void remove(java.lang.Comparable object,
          java.lang.Comparable attribute)
        Description copied from interface: Relation
        Removes the pair (object, attribute) from this relation.

        If object is null then attribute will be removed from the attribute set of this relation and all pairs whose attribute is attribute will be removed from this relation. Similarly, if attribute is null then object will be removed from the attribute set of this relation and all pairs whose object is object will be removed from this relation.

        Specified by:
        remove in interface Relation
        Parameters:
        object - the object.
        attribute - the attribute.
